><br><br><br>Earindil<br>Paladin of Tunare<br>6th Season<br>The Sea is calling nightly,<br>I wish to answer the call......<br>but something seems to keep me here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 4:21:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Try the Qeynos Hills, although there aren't huge numbers of rabid animals out there.<br><br>My beliefs are that if the animal attacks you, you have every right to defend yourself from it.  It's survival of the fittest, law of the jungle.  I won't attack anything that won't try to eat me for lunch, but lions...  well, we always want to have one another for lunch, it seems.<br><br>Lasgalen, Twentieth Autumn Initiate of Tunare and working on that Tailoring. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 4:32:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> The pelts dropped by rabid wolves/bears in QHills can't be used in tailoring. I'm pretty sure there are still rabid animals in the karanas, though. Particularly NK. And I think those drop normal pelts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=earindil>Earindil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 4:37:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Do wolves and bears have faction?<br> It seems they attack randomly, sometimes I can run over the top of a wolf and it keeps going and sometimes they attack. <p>Earindil<br />Paladin of Tunare<br />6th Season<br /><em>The Sea calls me nightly,I wish to answer the call.......but something seems to keep me here.</em><br /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 4:55:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Yes and no.<br><br>Don't kill bears or wolves in front of the Druids of Surefall Glades.<br><br>I'm not sure if there's any faction hit you take for killing them, the reason some attack you and some don't is that some are just not powerful enough to decide to take you on.  So they slink on by, instead.<br><br>Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usavahfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SavahFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 5:43:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Actually, we *can* kill cats. Lions don't like me, I don't like them... As simple as that. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>~Savah<BR>Ranger of Tunare<BR>Circle of Sisters</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utresjoli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tresjoli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.shadow-striders.com/images/wolfIcon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 5:45:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cpinternet.com/~theduke/MythStuff/ez-tres.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> An animal loving paladin?  You've missed your calling as a ranger or druid, but then I guess High Elves don't stoop to following such lowly pursuits.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>The only &quot;normal&quot; animals that I know of that have faction are those in Surefall Glade and Kithicor Forest.  (There are no wolves in Surefall Glade, btw, just bears.)  Many rangers and druids won't kill bears or wolves because they /consider amiably.  I've noticed, however, that wolves in Misty Thicket will assist bixies when they're attacked, even against druids.  I guess they see something in those annoying little buggers that the rest of us don't.  /giggle<br><br>Fighting bears or wolves near druids near the circle of stones in North Karana (I'm not certain about those in West Commonlands) will incur their wrath as well, even if you're only defending yourself.  <br><br>Holly Windstalker in Qeynos Hills will attack you if she sees you fighting a wolf or bear, whether they be &quot;healthy&quot; or rabid, or looting the corpse of a dead one.  Cros Treewind would, too, but I believe he longer roams QH.  I heard that he was perma killed.  /shrug<br><br> <p><b>Tresjoli Louveteau</b><br><i>Femme d'esprit</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubrimose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brimose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 11:26:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> I agree with my sister Savah... Cats are not the creation of Tunare.  Your deity will have no regrets with you should you decide to hunt lions, pumas, cougars, etc.  For my roleplaying purposes, I will always kill a wolf or bear if I am grouped with a brother or sister and he or she is attacked by the animal, and I rationalize it by suggesting that it must have been sick.  For tailoring purposes, I hunt cats for pelts and search the vendors for pelts from other animals.  When you decide you want to start making backpacks, then you have a choice to get those hq bear pelts:  spend a lot of money on one, or go to the Karanas and hope that a rabid grizzly will drop one (very rare off of these animals), or simply spend an hour or so out of character and don't tell anyone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br><br>Oh, and by the way, druids all over will attack you if you are fighting a wolf or bear, including commonlands.  Doesn't matter who started it.  Also, I've hunted rabid animals in QH and have never had a problem with Holly, you just need to glance around you every once in a while to make sure you're alone. <p>Brion (Raydon) <BR>15 Ranger of the Glade, Elder, Treasurer, and Charter Member of the Clan of Brothers on Fironia Vie <BR>Brimose Greymyst <BR>25 Ranger of the Glade, Nameless of Mercy on The Nameless, semi-retired <BR>Leaving my mark all over Norrath... in corpses <BR>Ack!  Ranger Down!</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubrimose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brimose</A> at: 1/29/02 11:28:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 334<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 11:32:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My hobbit druid slave ..</span><hr size=1> .. has no problems killing bears and wolves.  It is a druid's solemn duty to uphold the balance and prevent these creatures from overbreeding and decimating the poor rabbit population in Norrath.  When, may I ask, was the last time you even saw a rabbit on Antonica?  Never, I bet.  See what happens when you leave bears and wolves unchecked? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 12:23:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My hobbit druid slave ..</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;Cros Treewind would, too, but I believe he longer roams QH. I heard that he was perma killed.&gt;&gt;<br><br>So sayeth Illia, anyway.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=2988">eqbeastiary.allakhazam.co...ml?id=2988</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>(Edited to add the quote to which I was responding.) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A> at: 1/30/02 1:02:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator<br>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 350<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 12:28:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My hobbit druid slave ..</span><hr size=1> Go to Shadeweaver's Thicket and kill rockhoppers.  You can use rockhopper hides to make your armor.<br><br>Hope this helps with your quandry. <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>Taruun of Shar Val<BR><BR>Master Cook <BR>Lousy Fletcher<BR>Grandmaster Lech<BR><I>"I can picture in my mind a world without war, a world without hate. And I can picture us attacking that world, because they'd never expect it." -- Jack Handey</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 6:11:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wabbit Season!</span><hr size=1> I pull rabbit meat up with forage all the time.<br><br>Plenty of rabbits around.<br><br>Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueredhel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eredhel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 6:16:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wabbit Season!</span><hr size=1> You know I hadn't run across Cros in ages...but I hadn't even thought of it. Wierd that he's gone now.<br><br>Eredhel <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueredhel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eredhel</A> at: 1/30/02 6:16:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uguanofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GuanoFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 6:19:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wabbit Season!</span><hr size=1> Guano good at tailoring, guano make gnome skin armor and flayed human skin armor and eld hide gloves and troll hide belt.<br>  hahahahahahah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utwotribes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 7:04:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Tunare made all living things on Karana except for the so called intelligent races. Of the so called Intelligent races she created the Wood and High Elves.<br><br>Tunare is the Godess of Nature, Karana is the God of Rain , storm and such.<br><br>As a roleplay reason I see people expouse the no killing of certain animals. BUT only the Bears of Surefall are speciffically mentioned by any NPC as protected by Tunare, and even then Tunare doesnt say it, some of her followers do. One of the complaints that caused a rift between the Druids of Surefall and those of Rathe Mountains (unkempt) is the treatment of animals.<br><br>Nature is not good, nor is it evil. It just is.<br><br>Twotribes subscribes to the believe that it is the responsibility of the strong to use restraint when dealing with the weaker. There is no restriction, as far as he is concerned, on killing any animal, save that of conscious and need.  If you need something from an animal and there is no way to get it other than to kill it, so be it. Nature has always worked that way.<br><br>Bears of Surefall he will not attack (except to save a fool). But that is only because the local Druid Guild has proclaimed them protected. And he wont hunt animals for sport.<br><br>Only Druids and Rangers are protected from wolves and bears. No race (except maybe wood) has that distinction. A high Elf Paladin, Cleric or any class, will be attacked by most wolves and bears. There are exceptions of course. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 3:49:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Twotribes:<br><br>Actually, both Holly Windstalker, in the Qeynos Hills, and the Jaggedpine Cloak/Crook guy both forbid the killing of any of &quot;Tunare's Children&quot;.  In fact, he specifically forbade me to use the Crook on wolves or bears.<br><br>I always roleplayed that as if the Crook would break into its two components again if it were ever used on a wolf or bear.<br><br>Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhalus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Halus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 4:41:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wabbit Season!</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;&gt;I pull rabbit meat up with forage all the time.<br><br>Plenty of rabbits around.&lt;&lt;&lt;<br><br>You are obviously deluded about what you are eating. ... Those are just scraps left over from the lunch of some poor bear or wolf.<br><br>Halus<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utwotribes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 8:38:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Because a follower of a Diety says something..... doesnt make it so.  (thanks for pointing out some more specific NPCs that say that though)The Surefall Druids are fanatics (some of them). There is even a NPC in Surefall that wants the Mammoth to die. He provides a quest (with two possible ways to finish it, one requires killing the bear, the other allows a means to not kill the bear) This NPC is a worshipper of Tunare. <br><br>Why would a spell be allowed to exsist if it wasnt to be used? Charm Animal (which WILL agro the beast when worn off), Fear animal, are just two examples.<br><br>Twotribes, the character, does NOT see an absolute ban on killing animals. Such is not the will of Tunare, rather the desire of the followers in a portion of Norrath.<br><br>As for Woodelf and High Elf followers.... Humm, as I recall , one quest from the Paladin Hall in Felewith has the Paladins (or others) hunting wolves for their skin. And Some of the guilds in Kelethin also request you kill animals (wolves usually).<br><br>But that isnt the point. If you want to role play not killing certain animals, go ahead.... you decide what your character does. I am simply showing that it isnt a &quot;requirement&quot; of Tunare to not kill said beasts. And one COULD create all kinds of &quot;proof&quot; within the frame work of the game to support either idea.<br><br>IF you believe the death of wolves and Bears is bad, and wont hunt them...... Doesnt that make paying someone else (be it vendor or player) an act of ENCOURAGING the slaughter of said animals? Just a possible thought one could use to try to dissuade someone from either killing wolves or to be used to dissuade the practice of making armor from their pelts.<br><br>There are many many shades of how one can roleplay the concept of killing or not killing wolves and bears, I simply remind you that they arent the ONLY creations of Tunare (though if you want to roleplay it is, go ahead, just dont get upset if someone tries to convince you otherwise)<br><br>No I am not trying to tell anyone how to roleplay. I am simply providing information that may be used to help someone make a decision (if they wanted or needed info).<br><br>Back when EQ first started I had several heated discussions with people that tried to claim that roleplaying a druid (and Ranger)MEANT not killing animals, they used that arguement to try and prove that you couldnt roleplay in EQ. <br><br>The only absolutes are the game engine and a persons self imposed ones. And both can and do change over time.<br><br>So , to repeat. All this is MY interpretation, based on things I chose to believe. Each person has to decide their own path. And unless your path leads to harassing other players, it is a valid path. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 11:12:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Twotribes:<br><br>Don't get me wrong.  I believe that Nature is as bloodthirsty ('Red in tooth and claw&quot;, as Tennyson wrote) as it is tranquil.  Balance in all things.<br><br>I think those who think druids should not kill any animals are deluded.  But I only attack animals in self-defense, or those animals that would attack me (i.e., primarily cats).<br><br>I don't often buy wolf pelts or bear pelts.  I do for my own armor, but I don't make small sizes for anyone else unless they provide their own pelt (and I don't speak human well enough to sell large sizes to anyone).  Actually, for the studded I wear personally, I traded a bunch of cat pelts for a bunch of wolf pelts of the same quality with someone.<br><br>I certainly don't think these strictures apply necessarily to every worshiper of Tunare, and certainly, any being has a right to defend itself from attack.  That's survival of the fittest, which should be one of the prime tenets any follower of Tunare follows.<br><br>Lasgalen<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 12:29:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;Tunare made all living things on Karana except for the so called intelligent races.&gt;&gt;<br><br>If so, there are an awful lot of &quot;intelligent races&quot;: dragons, giants, orcs, goblins, kedge, &quot;all manner of creatures&quot; created by Brell Serilis, and Living Stone (whatver that is), to name a few.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/hht/history.jsp">everquest.station.sony.co...istory.jsp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utwotribes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 7:55:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1225.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring AND staying in character</span><hr size=1> Yes, I would have to say Brell made a Large number of races and things that reside underground ( Tunare populated the surface).<br><br>He secrettly made races that dwelt underground, he &quot;persuaded&quot; other dieties to make races so he wouldnt be alone faceing Veeshan. He then &quot;tricked&quot; others into making more races.  <br><br>He made Goblins, Dwarves, Gnomes for sure. I would venture to say he probably is responsible for several other races also. And as already stated, he made creatures underground. We may never see all his creations.<br><br>And there are , here and there, fantastical, magical creatures on the face of Norrath made by other Dieties. BUT Tunare created the vast majority of living species on the face of Norrath. She is after all &quot; The Mother of All&quot;<br><br>The so called intelligent races all have a diety that they can point to and say..... Made by .....   Except for Humans (also means Eruds) and Vah Shir. I suspect Vah SHir were created by a Diety and have just forgotton who that was. <br><br>Rallos Zek made Giants, Ogres and I believe Orcs. Others maybe also. <br><br>The Marr's made Barbarians. And I am sure there are some that suspect they had a hand in the creation of Humans. Eruds evolved from Humans.<br><br>Intelligent creature does not mean just those races that can be played by us.<br><br>It never hurts to read the information available about Norrath and Everquest. Thanks for a reference.<br><br>In Beta, at one point, Innorruuk was the original Diety of Elves.  A war insued and he and his faithful moved underground. At release that was changed to Tunare being the creator of Wood and High Elves, with Innorruuk stealing the Original King and Queen and torturing them for hundreds of years, eventually using the corrupted remains to create the Tier'Dal (Dark Elves). This bit of lore can easily be used to create an interesting tale or two by a Dark Elf, if they wanted to.<br><br>There are also conflicting lore on Troll creation. <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=1225.topic&start=21&stop=21>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href=